# Tiananmen Square Sarcastic YouTube Short

This plan details the process for generating a 90-second, high-retention YouTube Short using the `youtube-shorts-mastermind` skill. The video will employ a sarcastic, dry humor approach regarding the Tiananmen Square incident (e.g., repeating the punchline that "absolutely nothing happened"), narrated in Vietnamese using the ElevenLabs TTS API.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The plan proposes utilizing the ElevenLabs `eleven_multilingual_v2` model to synthesize Vietnamese audio. Please confirm if you have a specific ElevenLabs Voice ID you'd like to use for the dry, sarcastic tone, or if the default voice used in other scripts (e.g., `pNInz6obpgDQGcFmaJgB`) is acceptable.

## Proposed Changes

### Scripts & Asset Preparation
#### [NEW] `scripts/generate-voiceover-tiananmen.ts`
- Creates a script to iterate over 8-10 scenes of a sarcastic Vietnamese script (e.g., "N─ām 1989, tß║Īi quß║Żng trŲ░ß╗Øng Thi├¬n An M├┤n, mß╗Öt ─æiß╗üu v├┤ c├╣ng kß╗│ diß╗ću ─æ├Ż xß║Ży ra... ─æ├│ l├Ā kh├┤ng c├│ g├¼ xß║Ży ra cß║Ż.").
- Calls ElevenLabs API (`eleven_multilingual_v2` model) to synthesize the voice and estimate word-level timings.
- Outputs `.mp3` and `.json` (timings) files to `public/voiceover/tiananmen-square/`.

#### [NEW] `scripts/copy-media-tiananmen.ts`
- Scans `memeDatabase/GIF/` subdirectories (such as `suspicious/`, `everything-gone-chaos/`, `amazing-news/`).
- Copies and renames these GIFs to `public/images/tiananmen-square/scene-XX.gif` so they map perfectly to our `SCENES` array in the Remotion component.

---

### Remotion Components
#### [NEW] `src/components/TiananmenSquareShort.tsx`
- Copies the highly optimized template from `src/templates/YoutubeShortsMastermind.tsx`.
- Modifies `COMP_ID` to `"tiananmen-square"`.
- Updates the `SCENES` array with the translated/sarcastic Vietnamese text tags and corresponding scene IDs.
- Retrieves the Reddit payload (which will be swapped out for a mock or related sarcastic Reddit thread if available, or just removed).

#### [MODIFY] `src/Root.tsx`
- Registers the new `<Composition>` for `TiananmenSquareShort`.
- Points it to use `calculateMetadata` from `src/components/TiananmenSquareShort.tsx`.

## Open Questions

> [!WARNING]
> Do you have a preferred ElevenLabs Voice ID for the Vietnamese narration? Have you set `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` in your `.env`? (The existing trump script contains a hardcoded API key, which might be expired. Should I continue using it or expect an environment variable?)

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
1. Run `npx tsx scripts/generate-voiceover-tiananmen.ts` to verify the ElevenLabs API generates valid `.mp3` files in Vietnamese.
2. Run `npx tsx scripts/copy-media-tiananmen.ts` to align the GIFs logically.
3. Start the dev server `npm run dev` (or `npx remotion studio`) to verify that the template compiles, the pacing is fast, and the captions align accurately with the audio.

### Manual Verification
- Review the generated short in the Remotion Studio to ensure the dry/sarcastic tone is effectively communicated visually and audibly in the 9:16 layout without timeline issues.
